    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured as a "Curriculum Dashboard" rather than a linear document. This design prioritizes usability and conceptual understanding for the educator. The key sections are: 1) An "Overview" with a clickable "Unit at a Glance" grid for quick navigation. 2) A "Thematic Exploration" area that groups lessons by core concepts (Fear & Hysteria, Power & Oppression, Ideals & Identity) using accordions to manage information density. 3) An "Activity Toolkit" with filterable cards, allowing the user to find specific hands-on activities by intelligence type. This architecture transforms the lesson plan from a static script into a dynamic, reusable resource for planning and inspiration. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: Lesson plan activities and structure. -> Goal: Organize, Inform, Compare, Filter. -> Viz/Presentation Method: Interactive grid for navigation, collapsible accordions for daily plans, filterable cards for activities, and styled HTML/CSS for diagrams (Venn, T-Chart, Social Network). -> Interaction: Click-to-scroll navigation, expand/collapse accordions, and button-based filtering for the toolkit. -> Justification: These choices make a large amount of text-based information easily scannable and accessible, promoting exploration over linear reading. The toolkit filter adds significant value by making activities reusable. -> Library/Method: Vanilla JavaScript for all interactions. No Chart.js needed as there is no quantitative data. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
