            <div id="activity-grid" class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="kinesthetic interpersonal">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">The Human Rumor Mill</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">A game where a message is whispered around a circle to show how information gets distorted. (Day 1)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="kinesthetic interpersonal">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">The Hysteria Simulation</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">A mock "witch hunt" where students experience baseless accusation and a group trial. (Day 2)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="kinesthetic logical">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Human Timeline</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Students physically arrange themselves to represent a historical timeline of the Red Scare. (Day 4)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="kinesthetic visual interpersonal">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Living Tableaux</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Groups create frozen scenes ("tableaux") to represent key conflicts and symbols from Act II. (Day 4)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="interpersonal linguistic kinesthetic">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Courtroom Mock Trial</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Students take on roles from the Act III courtroom scene and improvise arguments. (Day 5)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="visual linguistic">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Gallery Walk</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Students circulate the room to analyze images and text related to a historical period. (Days 1, 6)</p>
                </div>
                 <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="musical linguistic">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Musical Reading</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Listen to contrasting musical pieces while reading a text to identify and feel mood shifts. (Day 6)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="logical interpersonal">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Document Detectives</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Small groups analyze excerpts of historical documents to deduce their core message and style. (Day 7)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="intrapersonal linguistic">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Found Poem</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Create a new poem using only words and phrases taken directly from source texts. (Day 7)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="activity-card bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200" data-type="visual intrapersonal">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">One-Pager / Visual Reflection</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">A single-page visual summary of a key concept, character, or event using drawings and quotes. (Days 5, 9)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="assessments" class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#8C6B52] mb-6">Assessments & Final Activities</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
